le Patients, Multiplicity of Lesions)\",\n      \"explanation\": \"Entities address cases that deviate from the standard operable paradigm, such as medically inoperable/high surgical risk individuals, directing them to definitive radiation therapy rather than surgery. Patients with suspected multiple lung cancers or separate pulmonary nodules are triaged through specific evaluation and staging steps, ensuring comprehensive assessment before definitive treatment [Data: Entities (191, 265, 54, 194); Relationships (448, 654, 121, 449, 656)].\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"summary\": \"Stepwise Progression Through NCCN Protocol Pages Reflects Standardized, Reproducible Care\",\n      \"explanation\": \"The extensive interconnectedness among protocol steps, captured as relationships between entities, ensures clinicians follow a structured, evidence-based decision tree that reduces ambiguity in patient care. For example, the movement from NSCL-2 to NSCL-8, then onward to specific advanced-stage pathways, is clearly codified in the relationships, providing a reproducible care pathway [Data: Entities (188, 196, 230, 61, 68); Relationships (439, 130, 635, 645, 155, +more)].\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"summary\": \"Technical Rigor, Biomarker Testing, and Imaging Are Embedded in Early Protocol Stages\",\n      \"explanation\": \"PRETREATMENT EVALUATION and EVALUATION nodes include advanced technical procedures such as EGFR, ALK, RET, and PD-L1 biomarker testing, along with high-resolution imaging (e.g., PET/CT, MRIs). These ensure that genetic and anatomical factors guide both staging and treatment in alignment with personalized medicine principles [Data: Entities (63, 55); Relationships (140, 139, 122, 121)].\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"summary\": \"Legal Compliance and Reputational Assurance Through Adherence to NCCN Guidelines\",\n      \"explanation\": \"All entities and their interconnections reflect current NCCN (National Comprehensive Cancer Network) guidelines, which are the le